1.5
log
@add a note about putting pwd.db into the chroot; c-client crashes without
it. there may be a better fix but document it for now, since this has bitten
multiple people (-:

ok mbalmer@@
@
text
@a7 6

To work inside a chroot, you must create files so that the userid
of the user running httpd may be looked up:

# grep ^www: /etc/master.passwd > ${PREFIX}/etc/master.passwd
# pwd_mkdb -d ${PREFIX}/etc ${PREFIX}/etc/master.passwd
